commit.message:
Remove use of deprecated 'setup.py test' command (#77)

Since setuptools v41.5.0 (27 Oct 2019), the 'test' command and its
arguments are formally deprecated and should not be used. Instead, use
the unittest module to run tests.

commit.message:
Remove deprecated license_file from setup.cfg (#79)

Starting with wheel 0.32.0 (2018-09-29), the "license_file" option is
deprecated.

https://wheel.readthedocs.io/en/stable/news.html

The wheel will continue to include LICENSE, it is now included
automatically:

https://wheel.readthedocs.io/en/stable/user_guide.html#including-license-files-in-the-generated-wheel-file

commit.message:
Check a-label does not contain a trailing hyphen (#64)

From RFC5891 § 4.2.1
 "If only an A-label was provided and the conversion to a U-label is
  not performed, the registry MUST still verify that the A-label is
  superficially valid, i.e., that it does not violate any of the rules
  of Punycode encoding [RFC3492] such as the prohibition on trailing
  hyphen-minus, (...)"
